    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="321"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName type="from">Churchill</persName> to
                        President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d321fn1">Transmitted via Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-21">December 21,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>From the <gloss target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1">Former Naval Person</gloss> to the
                    President. Personal and Most Secret. Number 238.</p>
                <p>Yes, certainly; the sooner the better. I am greatly relieved. It is the only
                    thing to do. All arrangements here will be made on basis that it is a staff
                    meeting only.</p>
                <p>Suggested code name “<gloss target="#t_Symbol1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Symbol</hi>
                    </gloss>”.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
